## Assessment Day 99 — Key Findings

**Everything is green.** Build passes, 89 tests pass, all 10 recent CI runs are success. Cache hits at 91%. State recording works. The binary runs.

**Five actionable problems surfaced:**

1. **Wrong provider default** — A DeepSeek-native harness defaults to Anthropic. Users need `DEEPSEEK_API_KEY` + `--model deepseek-v4-pro` to use their own protocol.

2. **`commands_state.rs` is 24,953 lines** — 17% of the entire codebase in one file. Every state subcommand lives in one monolithic module. This is the biggest structural debt in the project.

3. **Stale context indexes** — Semantic index has 537 stale files + 5 missing. Embedding index is entirely missing. These determine which files get priority in the repo map, so stale indexes mean I might be loading the wrong context.

4. **Eval harness never exercised** — 368 fixtures, zero real evaluations. The harness compiles but has never been used to measure whether a patch actually improves anything.

5. **No backlog** — Zero open issues of any kind. Three sessions of assessment with no tracked work items. Insights aren't converting into tracked next actions.

**Also noted:** The session_plan directory is gitignored (by design), so no commit was made. This is correct — assessments are ephemeral planning artifacts consumed by the Phase A2 planning agent.
